structure of data.level 2 Result block with n elements: [1 to n] each stands for results for one logicview file
structure of data.level 4/data block with 9 elements: [0]vector of polygon vectors, [1]vector of area calcs , [2]array of curvatures ,[3]vector of intersect coordinates upper aponeurosis, [4]vector of intersect coordinates deep aponeurosis , [5]vector of fascicle lengths (n elements in pixel), [6]vector of fascicle lengths (n elements in cm), [7]vector of angles at upper aponeurosis (n elements in degrees), [8]vector of angles at deep aponeurosis (n elements in degrees)  with n = number of fascicles
structure of data.level 5/polygons with n+2 elements: [0]vector of upper aponeurosis, [1]vector of deep aponeurosis, [2 to n+1] n vectors of fascicles
structure of data.level 6/polygons/vectors of fascicles wi: [0]vector number, [1]vector length, [2]vector with m elements (points in x-y-coordinats in pixel)
structure of data.level 5/area-results with 3 elements: [0]area[cm^2], [1]intercept point of aponeuroses [pixel coords], [2]center of area [pixel coords]
structure of data.level 5/curvatures with 3 elements: [0]vector of s-values along polygon[pixel], [1]vector in curvatures[1/m]; negative values are bending clockwise, [2]curvature of end segments
